<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-06-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="440" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d440">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 War Credits/672</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Greek Minister</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Simopoulos</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-06-30">June 30, 1934</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I am requested by the Secretary of the
                                Treasury to transmit to you a statement of the amounts due and
                                payable from your Government January 1, 1933, July 1, 1933, January
                                1, 1934, and July 1, 1934, pursuant to the terms of Part I of the
                                Debt Agreement of May 10, 1929, and Part I of the Moratorium
                                Agreement of May 24, 1932.</p>
                            <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">Statement of Amounts Due From the
                                    Government of Greece—January</hi> 1, 1933; <hi rend="smallcaps">July</hi> 1, 1933; <hi rend="smallcaps">January</hi> 1, 1934
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">and July</hi> 1, 1934.</p>
                            <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="italic">Amount due January 1,
                                1933:</hi></p>
                            <table cols="2" rows="1">
                                <row>
                                    <cell rendition="#hanging">Semi-annual interest due January 1,
                                        1933, on principal of bond No. 9 for $130,000 due July 1,
                                        1932, and postponed under Paragraph 2, Part I, of the
                                        debt-funding agreement of May 10, 1929</cell>
                                    <cell rendition="#bottom" role="num">$2,762.50</cell>
                                </row>
                            </table>
                            <pb facs="0641" n="541" xml:id="pg_541"/>
                            <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="italic">Amount due July 1, 1933:</hi></p>
                            <table cols="2" rows="4">
                                <row>
                                    <cell rendition="#hanging">Semi-annual interest for the period
                                        January 1 to July 1, 1933, on bond No. 9</cell>
                                    <cell rendition="#bottom" role="num">$2,762.50</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell rendition="#hanging">Semi-annual interest due July 1,
                                        1933, on principal of bond No. 10 for $130,000 due January
                                        1, 1933, and postponed under Paragraph 2, Part I, of the
                                        debtfunding agreement of May 10, 1929</cell>
                                    <cell rendition="#bottom" role="num">$2,762.50</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell rendition="#hanging">Semi-annual interest due July 1,
                                        1933, under Paragraph I (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) of the
                                        Moratorium Agreement of May 24, 1932, as authorized by the
                                        Joint Resolution of the Congress of the United States
                                        approved December 23, 1931</cell>
                                    <cell rendition="#bottom #border-bottom" role="num">$13,169.45</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell/>
                                    <cell role="num">$18,694.45</cell>
                                </row>
                            </table>
                            <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="italic">Amount due January 1,
                                1934:</hi></p>
                            <table cols="2" rows="5">
                                <row>
                                    <cell rendition="#hanging">Semi-annual interest for the period
                                        July 1, 1933 to January 1, 1934 on bond No. 9</cell>
                                    <cell rendition="#bottom" role="num">$7,762.50</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell rendition="#hanging">Semi-annual interest for the period
                                        July 1, 1933 to January 1, 1934 on bond No. 10</cell>
                                    <cell rendition="#bottom" role="num">2,762.50</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell rendition="#hanging">Semi-annual interest due January 1,
                                        1934 on principal of bond No. 11 for $150,000 due July 1,
                                        1933, and postponed under Paragraph 2, Part I, of the
                                        debt-funding agreement of May 10, 1929</cell>
                                    <cell rendition="#bottom" role="num">3,187.50</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell rendition="#hanging">Semi-annual instalment due January 1,
                                        1934 under the Moratorium Agreement of May 24, 1932</cell>
                                    <cell rendition="#bottom #border-bottom" role="num">13,169.45</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell/>
                                    <cell role="num">$21,881.95</cell>
                                </row>
                            </table>
                            <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="italic">Amount payable July 1,
                                1934:</hi></p>
                            <table cols="3" rows="6">
                                <row>
                                    <cell rendition="#hanging">Semi-annual interest for the period
                                        January 1 to July 1, 1934, on bond No. 9</cell>
                                    <cell rendition="#bottom" role="num">$2,762.50</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell rendition="#hanging">Semi-annual interest for the period
                                        January 1 to July 1, 1934, on bond No. 10</cell>
                                    <cell rendition="#bottom" role="num">2,762.50</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell rendition="#hanging">Semi-annual interest for the period
                                        January 1 to July 1, 1934, on bond No. 11</cell>
                                    <cell rendition="#bottom" role="num">3,187.50</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell rendition="#hanging">Semi-annual interest due July 1,
                                        1934, on principal of bond No. 12 for $150,000 due January
                                        1, 1934, and postponed under Paragraph 2, Part I, of the
                                        debt-funding agreement of May 10, 1929</cell>
                                    <cell rendition="#bottom" role="num">3,187.50</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell rendition="#hanging">Semi-annual instalment due July 1,
                                        1934, under the Moratorium Agreement of May 24, 1932</cell>
                                    <cell rendition="#bottom #border-bottom" role="num">13,169.45</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell/>
                                    <cell rendition="#bottom" role="num">$25,069.45</cell>
                                </row>
                            </table>
                            <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/><signed>R. <hi rend="smallcaps">Walton Moore</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>